Title: Negative Probability and Uncertainty Relations
Authors: Thomas Curtright and Cosmas Zachos
Comments: RevTeX, 4 pages
Report-no: ANL-HEP-PR-01-034, Miami TH/1/01
Subj-class: High Energy Physics - Theory; Mathematical Physics
Journal-ref: Mod.Phys.Lett. A16 (2001) 2381-2385
\\
  A concise derivation of all uncertainty relations is given entirely within
the context of phase-space quantization, without recourse to operator methods,
to the direct use of Weyl's correspondence, or to marginal distributions of x
and p.
